<br>
&quot; Elandril, just the man I was looking for.&quot;<br>
<br>
His face showed his momentary surprise before recognition of her voice registered. A smile spread across his lips as he stood straight at her approach. &quot; Tero!  Good to see you.&quot; He chuckled at his own joke. &quot; What brings ya this way?<br>
<br>
With great difficulty, Terolyn swallowed the desire to gut him where he stood and forced a smile onto her face. Speaking as pleasantly as she good she answered. &quot; Just passing through and heard you were in the area. I thought we could have a drink or two, catch up since we haven’t seen each other in a while…&quot;<br>
<br>
His smile widened. &quot; Sure, sounds good. I believe I got some Blackburrow stout-&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot; I’ve got something better,&quot; She rummaged through her pack, retrieving the wine skin. &quot; I borrowed this from Dey’s private stash.  Doubt she will miss it.&quot; She removed the cork from the skin.<br>
<br>
Minz sniffed like an animal at the air, an impish look  in his eyes. &quot;  Um, easy there hon, that’s strong stuff.&quot; <br>
<br>
She chuckled darkly. &quot; What’s the matter? Not stomach for the good stuff?&quot;  Finding it harder to <br>
restrain herself Terolyn dug once more into her pack. The two goblets clinked against one another as she lifted them out of the sack.<br>
<br>
&quot; And glasses too,&quot; Minz snickered. &quot; Wow, to what do we owe the occasion?&quot;<br>
<br>
Her eyes never left his face as she poured the wine into the first goblet and placed it in his hand. &quot; No occasion.&quot; She emptied the skin into the second glass, her face now as cold and emotionless as the crystal of the goblets. &quot; I just a good drink now and then, don’t you?&quot;<br>
<br>
He did not seem to notice the subtle chance in the tone of her voice and raised the glass in a toast. &quot; Cheers!&quot;<br>
<br>
With a tap of her glass to his, Terolyn smirked. &quot; To your health…&quot;<br>
<br>
The sweet smelly liquid had barely passed his lips before he lowered the glass, his eyes narrowing. He swallowed the fluid in his mouth, holding the glass beneath his nose and inhaling deeply. &quot; What’s - what the-?!&quot; The goblet fell from his hand, shattering when it hit the ground. &quot;Poison?!&quot;<br>
<br>
An annoyed growl escaped her and grabbing him before he could react she slammed him against the stone wall, her dirk suddenly pressed dangerously against his throat. &quot; It would have been easier if you had just drank the wine.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot; You’ll pay Tero,&quot; He face twisted into a sneer<br>
<br>
&quot; Drink!&quot; She forced the rim of her glass between his lips and began to pour the wine into his mouth. He shook his head violently, knocking the goblet from her hand.  The next instant he spat the wine in his mouth directly into her face. Alcohol burned her eyes and he punched her viciously in the abdomen, sending her stumbling back a few paces.<br>
<br>
His breathing was coming in rapid gasps, the confusion and anger apparent on his face as he drew his harpoon from his back and a dagger from the folds of his cloak. &quot; I won’t go down easily&quot;<br>
<br>
Terolyn wiped the moisture from her face, drawing her stiletto from her belt. &quot; More fun for me then!&quot;<br>
<br>
She ducked under a swing of his harpoon, buying time until the pit of wine he had drank took affect. The deadly dance began, the ringing of their blades echoing through the mountains. Her blades sunk into his flesh, as did his gouge into her. Terolyn crouched beneath another attack of the harpoon, but was not quick enough to move away from the slashing dagger as he moved behind her. Metal bit through her sleeves and into her arm. In the same motion he tore the blade from her, moving the shaft of his harpoon over her waist and pulling her against him, and held the bloodied dagger at her throat. &quot; Enough!&quot;<br>
<br>
Both rogues were breathing hard, but she could sense the tiring of his muscles in his weakening hold on her. &quot; What’s the matter Minz? You’re looking a little tired.&quot;<br>
<br>
He snarled. &quot; Bite me!&quot;<br>
<br>
A wolfish grin filled her features. &quot; If you insist!&quot; Terolyn took hold of the arm with the dagger in hand and sunk her teeth into his wrist. He hollered out in pain, the weapon falling from his fingers. Minz pushed her away as she laughed, spitting the salty blood from her lips. With a feral scream she spun around, the blunt end of her stiletto’s hilt cracking against Minz’s temple. <br>
<br>
A soft moan of pain and he crumpled to the ground into unconsciousness.  <br>
<br>
Emerald eyes flashed dangerously as she stood above the helpless Pendragon, the grin never fading. &quot; Nighty night, Minzy.&quot; <br>
<br>
